Sixty-third Avenue (foreground not shown) east of 97th Street (about 56 ft.) showing in three views the H. Vanderveer house of 1873. H.S. and H.G. Vanderveer were the owners in 1891 and 1909 respectively. It was erected by Henry Suydam Vanderveer in 1850 and remodeled and enlarged by him in 1873. J. Vanderveer was the owner in 1896. In 1923 it was John Vanderveers residence. The rear building seen in view No. 3 is 47-09 Sixty-third Drive.

April 1923

View 3: March 1925
